  "body": "**What would you like to be added**:\r\nA consistent way for adding extended functionality to plugins.\r\n\r\n**Why is this needed**:\r\nCurrently we have two types of plugins that support adding some sort of optional functionality: PreFilter allow adding \"AddPod/RemovePod\" implementations through an \"Updater\" interface, while Score includes a NormalizeScore, which must be implemented, but plugins that don't require it can return nil.\r\n\r\nThe two cases above support adding \"optional\" functionality in different ways, what I suggest we do is have a common pattern, with common naming conventions to support that:\r\n\r\nAny plugin that needs an extended functionality should define an ```_PluginName_Extensions``` interface, and have a method named ```Extensions()``` that returns the interface or nil if the plugin does not implement those extensions.\r\n\r\nIf we do that for PreFilter and Score plugins, it would look like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntype PreFilterExtensions interface {\r\n\tAddPod(pc *PluginContext, podToSchedule *v1.Pod, podToAdd *v1.Pod, nodeInfo *schedulernodeinfo.NodeInfo) *Status\r\n\tRemovePod(pc *PluginContext, podToSchedule *v1.Pod, podToRemove *v1.Pod, nodeInfo *schedulernodeinfo.NodeInfo) *Status\r\n}\r\n\r\ntype PreFilterPlugin interface {\r\n\tPlugin\r\n\tPreFilter(pc *PluginContext, p *v1.Pod) *Status\r\n\tExtensions() PreFilterExtensions\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\ntype ScoreExtensions interface {\r\n    NormalizeScore(pc *PluginContext, p *v1.Pod, scores NodeScoreList) *Status\r\n}\r\n\r\ntype ScorePlugin interface {\r\n\tPlugin\r\n        Score(pc *PluginContext, p *v1.Pod, nodeName string) (int, *Status)\r\n\tExtensions() PreFilterExtensions\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOne concern here is that if the plugin wants to implement a single method of the extensions interface, they it will have to implement all the extensions methods, but i think that is fine since we don't expect to have many methods anyways.\r\n\r\n",
